text:
My view on the market fall:
1. FED taper is clearly a factor and impacts the liquidity in the market. Both FIIs and HNI/ DIIs who have low cost easy access to funds since Mar 2020 will reallocate funds. FED taper will be a major driver and when market corrects, the hot money of retail investors who jumped on the equity bandwagon in last 2 years will also get jittery. 
2. Concerns over Russia Ukraine, China Taiwan as geopolitical risks, and also the fallout on oil markets. The sharp rise in oil already points to a weaker fiscal deficit scenario for India. 
I would look at Nifty at 16500 and 14500 levels and buy quality at both these levels.
